David Sternlight (strnlght@netcom.com) wrote:

: If they keep their word, they can't tap your line until they already have a
: court order. Thus they won't have access to any traffic prior to the court
: order. That's easily checked in any legal proceeding against you, so they
: wouldn't even try. 

Come again?  How to you prove that they tapped your line, especially as
they will be able to do it long distance with the FBI wiretap bill?
And remember -- the NSA needs no stinkin' badges.


: In other words, they need evidence other than your past "broken" traffic to
: get the court order in the first place, and even if they cheat and have
: prior traffic, they can't use it in court since it would amount to a guilty
: plea of violating the wiretap laws and the evidence would also be
: suppressable.

But if they use the tap simply to develop more leads, how do you prove that
the new leads were the fruit of a poisoned tree?


